body.name: CORSAIR Dominator Titanium RGB DDR5 RAM 64GB (4x16GB) DDR5 6400MHz CL32 Intel XMP iCUE Compatible Computer Memory - White (CMP64GX5M4B6400C32W)
body.stockDetail: Only 7 left in stock (more on the way).
features: Sophisticated Styling, Premium Quality: Clean, refined styling combines with premium forged aluminum construction, for quality you can feel.
Beyond the Cutting Edge of Performance: Push your system to new heights with the latest DDR5 memory, unlocking even faster frequencies, greater capacities, and better performance.
11 Vibrant Addressable RGB LEDs: Each module boasts 11 individually addressable LEDs to illuminate your PC with spectacular customizable lighting.
Swappable Top Bar: Time for a new look? Change your memory’s style and cooling capacity with official accessories or 3D print your own top bar for your own unique style.
Patented CORSAIR DHX Cooling: Cools the memory through both the ICs and the ground plane of the PCB itself with its own dedicated heatspreader, ensuring high performance even under extreme loads.
body.description: CORSAIR DOMINATOR TITANIUM DDR5 Memory combines clean, refined styling with superior forged aluminum construction and vibrant RGB lighting for a premium memory experience. Tightly-screen high-frequency, low latency memory chips backed by patented CORSAIR DHX cooling ensure your system can handle complex tasks faster and smoother than ever. Preset and custom dynamic RGB lighting profiles via CORSAIR iCUE Murals software make the most of the 11-zone RGB LEDs featured on each module, while setting your memory to its optimal speed is easy thanks to support for Intel XMP 3.0. With its elegant styling and premium construction, DOMINATOR TITANIUM sets the standard by which others are judged.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Flawless RAM Upgrade – Corsair Nails It!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I recently made a significant RAM upgrade for my ASUS z790 Hero motherboard, switching from 2 sticks of Corsair Dominator 32GB 6200 RAM to the Corsair Titanium 64GB 6400 RAM – and the results have been nothing short of amazing!First and foremost, the installation was a breeze. I popped all four sticks into the motherboard, and they were recognized immediately. The memory retrained effortlessly, and I was up and running at the full 6400MHz right out of the box. No hassles, no headaches – just plug and play. Corsair really hit the mark with this one!The performance boost has been substantial. Everything from gaming to multitasking has seen a noticeable improvement. Running memory-intensive applications is a breeze, and I no longer experience any slowdowns or lag. The Corsair Titanium RAM has made my computing experience smoother and more efficient than ever before.What's even more impressive is that everyone has heard about the horror stories of running quad-channel RAM and XMP profiles having issues, but not with these sticks. They have been rock solid from day one, and I haven't encountered a single hiccup. It's reassuring to know that I made the right choice with Corsair.Aside from the incredible performance, these sticks also look fantastic with their sleek design and built-in RGB lighting. It's a small touch, but it adds a lot to the overall aesthetics of my setup.Corsair has always been a trusted brand for me, and this product reaffirms why. The quality and reliability are top-notch, and I couldn't be happier with this RAM upgrade. It's a definite game-changer for anyone looking to boost their PC's performance without any hassle.In conclusion, if you're in the market for high-performance RAM that delivers as promised, the Corsair Titanium 64GB 6400 RAM is the way to go. Easy installation, blazing fast speeds, and Corsair's reputation for quality make this a winning choice. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good looking, works with AMD at 6400MHz, *very* tall
reviews.reviewText: These sticks look nice and I was able to get them working with their stock EXPO/XMP profile (the 6400MHz one, not the 6600MHz one) on my Asus X670E ProArt motherboard (BIOS 0805, anything newer fails to POST with non-JEDEC speeds for me) & 7950X. I was actually pretty surprised it managed over 6000MHz. As for the DIMMS, they look nice, the RGB customization seems very good (lots of effects, very bright but can be dimmed, and easy to use). My only complaints/ warnings is that they are tall. They might interfere with your cooler or at the very least, block the fan a bit. I'm not super concerned with my U14S, but a dual tower cooler might have issues. I've included a comparison with a much lower profile set of DDR5.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I 100% misread the site my motherboard came from when I checked to see if my computer could handle this stuff before I got it. Unfortunately, it just can’t. It’s really disappointing. These things are beautiful and I’m certain that they would be glorious if my system could handle them.

Die Speichersticks sind hochwertig verarbeitet und ließen sich sofort mit der iCUE-Software ansprechen. Die Leistung ist ebenfalls sehr gut, ich bin sehr zufrieden mit dem Gesamteindruck meines PCs. Das Design bewertet jeder subjektiv, mir persönlich gefällt es sehr gut, weil es dezent und dennoch Gaming-PC-like ist.Im Vorfeld sollte man sich unbedingt erkundigen, wie viele Slots das Mainboard verträgt bzw. welche Variante. Die offizielle Homepage bzw. der Kundenservice helfen hier schnell weiter.
